{
  "stem": "24614.6",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Not I'm losing him because he doesn't want me anymore, but wherever I go, something is happening.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And he shows me this letter, this telegram.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "I think I have it on the table.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And I say, you have to go home.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Your father needs you.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And, when are you going to come?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Whenever the Army will bring me, I'll come.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know, I was a war bride.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was away from Danny for six months, separated after only being married for a month or so.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We wrote to each other every day.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "His father wrote to me love letters, what his son is telling him about me.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "His mother, I never got a letter from.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Danny, when he came back-- his father was very, very sick-- started working for the Zionist movement-- went back to the University of Pennsylvania, of course, after he was discharged.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And got there his master's, his bachelor's, his PhD, whatever.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he wrote to me everything.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I mean, every day.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But the meantime, I was sitting on Stadien Street, on the steps, waiting every day for a letter from Danny.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "If the letter, god forbid, didn't come that day and the next day came too, I was back in the Holocaust and maybe worse.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My mother and all of us had to worry for every day a piece of bread still, because we didn't get yet anything.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Later on we got a little help.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They gave everybody a little help, the Jewish gemeinde.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And my wedding, if I would describe it, would take over a half hour, maybe more.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But I felt, and so did Danny feel, through my letters, through his letters that I read, that we're going to have a very rich life together.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
